race.comment: GOLDEN AGE (6) is well and truly overdue. Has been an age since a win but recent form has been strong without breaking through. Placed in a 50k BM78 two back then close-up fourth in a 60k race last time. This looks ideal and is expected to go close again. MONT SAINT MICHEL (2) is back in grade but also back in trip and jumps from a wide gate. Will spot a start this sharper journey but has the ability to run on into the finish. ARABIAN MYTH (1) has been building towards a win and wasn't beaten far last time. This suits and should feature with a repeat of the latest effort. SOTOMAYOR (4) returns from a break on the back of two jump-outs. Best form stacks up and should run well. PALENTINE'S DAY (7) true din a nice run fresh and strips fitter. Among the leading chances.
